5. Scheduling and access 
SLURM manages both Computational Chemistry nodes. Partitions reflect workload class and QoS reflects priority. Persistent inference services run continuously under the always-on QoS rather than being scheduled per request. Pre-emption on INSIIUKCGPU01 prevents services from being blocked by short batch jobs on the same node. Fairshare on INSIIUKGPU01 shares GPU research time among Computational Chemistry users. Access is restricted to the cheminformatics SLURM sub-account; bioinformatics and statistical genetics workloads run on INSIIUKCPU01 and INSIIUKGPU02 in the shared research pool. 
