Critical path and delivery risks 
The critical path runs through pre-conditions, foundation, SLURM, licensed software, internal APIs, and external access, in that order. Parallel tracks (Spack and container builds, API code, user documentation) overlap with this path and shorten elapsed time but do not change the sequence. 
Delivery-specific risks not already covered in section 6: 
•	IT throughput on LDAP, DNS, and tunnel provisioning. Out of our direct control. Mitigated by parallel-tracking Nick’s work on anything that does not depend on it. 
•	Schrödinger and OpenEye licence binding. Hardware-bound and MAC-locked respectively. Coordinate timing with each vendor’s support before Phase 3 to avoid activation lag becoming the critical path. 
•	First-month accounting noise. Early utilisation data is unreliable while users adapt to the system. Validation of per-job budgets is therefore scheduled for the second month, not the first. 

